{
  "texts": [
    "The reward function of a representative follower is r f: S × A × B × ∆ S → [0, 1], with the understanding here that S is restricted to S f. Similarly, the reward of the leader r l: S × B × ∆ S → [0, 1] does not depend on the state of the representative follower s f, but only on the mean field.",
    "The state and action spaces of all players is assumed to be finite to enable the analysis, but continuous space approximations are studied experimentally in Section 5.Followers' Interaction.",
    "The followers play a mean field game in response to a policy ϕ: S → ∆ B of the leader.",
    "As in a standard MFG, let the representative follower take actions according to a randomized policy π: S → ∆ A.",
    "Given a leader-follower policy pair (ϕ, π) and a mean field µ, the sequentially generated states form a Markov chain, for which the transition matrix is P π,ϕ,µ ∈ R |S|×|S|."
  ]
}